text: The Laguna Volcanic Field, also known as the San Pablo Volcanic Field, is an active volcanic field in the Philippines, located between Laguna de Bay, Mount Banahaw volcano complex and Mount Malepunyo range. It is part of the larger Southwestern Luzon Volcanic Field (SWLVF). From Manila, it is about southeast of Mount Makiling. ==References== ==Other websites== * Global Volcanism Program * Philippines Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (PHIVOLCS) Category:Geography of the Philippines Category:Volcanoes of the Philippines Category:Laguna (province)
